cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language understanding and question-answering. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of neural networks to learn a natural language interface. Additionally, since the interface is designed to interact with a database, it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) as well. Finally, since the model is trained using weak supervision, it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
